    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), a pinnacle of analog feedback. This example is powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six, utilizing VarioCam Plus for a broad power band and 320hp. The G96 6-speed manual transaxle provides crisp engagement, paired with a factory M030 sport suspension for superior lateral stability and transient response. Mechanical integrity is paramount: the IMS bearing has been proactively replaced with a dual-row ceramic retrofit, and the bore-scope inspection shows zero scoring. The exterior retains its factory depth with no swirl marks, while the underbody remains free of corrosion or fluid seepage. This is a turn-key, high-compression masterpiece for the purist who demands mechanical transparency.",
